GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 920
Short Title: SNAP Administrative Funding/Forsyth County. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Lowe (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
April 30, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT APPROPRIATING FUNDS TO FORSYTH COUNTY TO COVER THE LOSS OF
3 FEDERAL RECEIPTS FOR THE ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS OF THE FEDERAL
4 SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM (SNAP) AS A RESULT OF
5 PUBLIC LAW 119-21.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
8 Health and Human Services, Division of Social Services (Division), the sum of three million
9 eight hundred eighty-eight thousand ten dollars ($3,888,010) in nonrecurring funds for the
10 2026-2027 fiscal year to cover the loss of federal receipts for the administrative costs of the
11 federal Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) as a result of Public Law 119-21.
12 The Division shall allocate these funds to the Forsyth County Department of Social Services to
13 cover the loss of federal receipts for the administrative costs of SNAP as a result of Public Law
14 119-21. The Division shall only allocate the portion of these appropriated funds up to the actual
15 amount of lost federal receipts.
16 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*S920-v-1*

